{"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"metadata":{"category":"Building SyncUps","estimatedTime":"3hr 10min","categoryPathComponent":"BuildingSyncUps","role":"overview","title":"Building SyncUps"},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/BuildingSyncUps","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[],"reference":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/BuildingSyncUps"},"sections":[{"kind":"hero","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The SyncUps application is a recreation of one of Apple’s more interesting demo applications,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Scrumdinger. We recreate it from scratch using the Composable Architecture, with a focus on","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"domain modeling, controlling dependencies, and testability."}]}],"title":"Building SyncUps","action":{"isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Get started","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/WhatIsSyncUps","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"Get started","type":"text"}],"type":"reference"}},{"image":null,"chapters":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s start with a tour of the application we will be building. It’s called SyncUps, and it’s a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"recreation of the Apple’s Scrumdinger demo application.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"tutorials":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/WhatIsSyncUps"],"image":"chapter1.png","name":"What is SyncUps?"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"We will begin building the SyncUps app from scratch by implementing the feature that powers the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"list of sync-ups. It starts out as a simple feature, but it will become increasingly complex as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the app evolves."}]}],"tutorials":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/ListsOfSyncUps","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingListOfSyncUps"],"name":"Lists of sync-ups","image":"chapter2.png"},{"name":"New sync-up form","image":"chapter3.png","tutorials":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/SyncUpForm","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingSyncUpForm"],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Let’s build a new feature for editing the details of a sync-up in a form. This will allow us to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"explore the binding tools the library provides, and we will add some complex logic around focus"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in the form, and show how it is 100% testable.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"image":"chapter4.png","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"We now have two features built, the sync-ups list and the sync-up form. These features do not"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"exist in isolation, but rather are meant to be integrated in a deep way. One should be able to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"navigate to the sync-up form from the list view, enter the details of a new sync-up, and then","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"add that sync-up to the root list."}]}],"tutorials":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/PresentingSyncUpForm","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingSyncUpFormPresentation"],"name":"Presenting the sync-up form"},{"tutorials":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/PersistingSyncUps"],"image":"chapter5.png","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Applications typically need to persist data across application launches. The Composable"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Architecture comes with tools to help you persist your application’s data."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Persisting sync-ups to disk"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The next feature to build is the “detail” screen for a sync-up. This feature allows the user to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"edit a sync-up, record a new meeting, see past recorded meetings, and even delete the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"sync-up."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Sync-up detail","tutorials":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/SyncUpDetail","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/EditingAndDeletingSyncUp","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingSyncUpDetail"],"image":"chapter6.png"},{"image":"chapter7.png","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"We now have a sync-up detail screen, but still no way to navigate to it from the rest of the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"app. We want to be able to drill-down to the detail screen from the list screen.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"tutorials":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/SyncUpDetailNavigation","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/MeetingNavigation","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingNavigation"],"name":"Navigating to sync-up detail"},{"tutorials":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/RecordMeetingFeature","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/ImplementingTimer","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/ImplementingSpeechRecognizer"],"name":"Record meeting","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The app is almost complete! But we have saved the most difficult feature for last: recording"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a new meeting. This requires interfacing with two complex dependencies, a speech recognizer"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and timer, and requires some subtle behavior that we are definitely going to want to get","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"test coverage on."}]}],"image":"chapter8.png"}],"content":[],"kind":"volume","name":null}],"kind":"overview","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/tutorials\/buildingsyncups"]}],"references":{"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/TestingNavigation":{"url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/testingnavigation","kind":"project","title":"Testing navigation","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"We have now implemented a navigation stack at the root of our application, and integrated"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"3 features into the stack: the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SyncUpsList"},{"text":" feature, the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SyncUpDetail"},{"type":"text","text":" feature, and the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"MeetingView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". Some of these features have quite complex logic binding them together, such as","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"when one deletes a sync-up from the detail screen it should pop the screen off the stack.","type":"text"}],"role":"project","estimatedTime":"10min","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingNavigation"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/ImplementingSpeechRecognizer":{"url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/implementingspeechrecognizer","kind":"project","title":"Adding a speech recognizer","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"We have just one feature left to implement, and it’s one of the most complicated ones. We need"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to use Apple’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SFSpeechRecognizer"},{"text":" API to ask the user for permission to transcribe their","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"audio, and then start a speech recognition task to live transcribe the meeting while it is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in progress."}],"role":"project","estimatedTime":"10min","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/ImplementingSpeechRecognizer"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/TestingSyncUpFormPresentation":{"role":"project","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingSyncUpFormPresentation","type":"topic","title":"Testing the add sync-up flow","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/testingsyncupformpresentation","estimatedTime":"10min","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"We have now integrated two moderately complex features, the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SyncUpsList"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SyncUpForm"},{"text":", and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"so its time to write some tests. This will give us the opportunity to prove that the features"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"work in tandem as we expect, and we will explore “non-exhaustive” testing to make our tests less"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"fragile."}],"kind":"project"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/EditingAndDeletingSyncUp":{"role":"project","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/EditingAndDeletingSyncUp","type":"topic","title":"Editing and deleting a sync-up","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/editinganddeletingsyncup","estimatedTime":"30min","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s implement two major pieces of functionality in the detail screen: editing the sync-up and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"deleting the sync-up. This will force us to face a number of common problems in app development"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"all at once, including view reuse, navigation, alerts, and parent-child communication patterns.","type":"text"}],"kind":"project"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/TestingSyncUpForm":{"url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/testingsyncupform","kind":"project","title":"Testing the sync-up form","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"We now have a moderately complex feature for editing the details of a sync-up, the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SyncUpForm"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reducer. Let’s get some test coverage on the feature, and doing so will force us to come"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"face-to-face with dependencies for the first time in this tutorial.","type":"text"}],"role":"project","estimatedTime":"10min","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingSyncUpForm"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/ImplementingTimer":{"role":"project","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/ImplementingTimer","type":"topic","title":"Adding a meeting timer","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/implementingtimer","estimatedTime":"25min","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The first major piece of logic and behavior we will introduce to the record meeting feature is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the timer. This is a long-living effect that runs in parallel with the rest of the feature, and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"we need to implement nuanced logic to figure out when to proceed to the next speaker.","type":"text"}],"kind":"project"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/ListsOfSyncUps":{"role":"project","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/ListsOfSyncUps","type":"topic","title":"Lists of sync-ups","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/listsofsyncups","estimatedTime":"10min","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"We will begin building the SyncUps app from scratch by implementing the feature that powers the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"list of sync-ups. It starts out as a simple feature, but it will become increasingly complex as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the app evolves.","type":"text"}],"kind":"project"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/SyncUpDetail":{"role":"project","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/SyncUpDetail","type":"topic","title":"Sync-up detail","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/syncupdetail","estimatedTime":"5min","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The “sync-up detail” screen shows all the information of a sync-up, and has many actions that"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"can take place in the screen. The user can edit the sync-up, or start a new meeting in the sync"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"up, or drill-down to a past meeting, or even delete the meeting.","type":"text"}],"kind":"project"},"chapter1.png":{"identifier":"chapter1.png","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/ComposableArchitecture\/chapter1.png"}],"alt":null,"type":"image"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/BuildingSyncUps":{"role":"overview","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/BuildingSyncUps","type":"topic","title":"Building SyncUps","url":"\/tutorials\/buildingsyncups","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The SyncUps application is a recreation of one of Apple’s more interesting demo applications,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Scrumdinger. We recreate it from scratch using the Composable Architecture, with a focus on"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"domain modeling, controlling dependencies, and testability.","type":"text"}],"kind":"overview"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/MeetingNavigation":{"url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/meetingnavigation","kind":"project","title":"Navigating to a meeting","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Now that we have a navigation stack in place we can start navigating to other features in the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"application. The simplest is the meeting screen, which allows you to see the details of a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"previous recorded meeting.","type":"text"}],"role":"project","estimatedTime":"5min","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/MeetingNavigation"},"chapter5.png":{"identifier":"chapter5.png","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/ComposableArchitecture\/chapter5.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":null,"type":"image"},"chapter6.png":{"identifier":"chapter6.png","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/ComposableArchitecture\/chapter6.png"}],"alt":null,"type":"image"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/PersistingSyncUps":{"role":"project","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/PersistingSyncUps","type":"topic","title":"Persisting sync-ups","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/persistingsyncups","estimatedTime":"5min","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Now that we have the ability to add and remove sync-ups from the application, let’s add some"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"persistence. This will involve using the “shared state” tools from the library, such as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"@Shared","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fileStorage"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"kind":"project"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/RecordMeetingFeature":{"url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/recordmeetingfeature","kind":"project","title":"The RecordMeeting feature","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s get the basics of a new feature into place that we can navigate to, and then we will"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"slowly layer on its complex logic and behavior, such as the timer and speech recognizer."}],"role":"project","estimatedTime":"5min","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/RecordMeetingFeature"},"chapter3.png":{"identifier":"chapter3.png","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/ComposableArchitecture\/chapter3.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":null,"type":"image"},"chapter7.png":{"identifier":"chapter7.png","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/ComposableArchitecture\/chapter7.png"}],"alt":null,"type":"image"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/TestingSyncUpDetail":{"role":"project","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingSyncUpDetail","type":"topic","title":"Testing the sync-up detail","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/testingsyncupdetail","estimatedTime":"10min","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SyncUpDetail"},{"type":"text","text":" feature has slowly become quite complex. It now handles two forms of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"navigation (an alert and sheet), it models navigation state with a single enum, and it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"communicates with a parent feature via delegate actions. It’s about time we got some test"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"coverage on this feature so we can be sure it works as we expect, and so that we can make future"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"changes with confidence."}],"kind":"project"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/SyncUpDetailNavigation":{"url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/syncupdetailnavigation","kind":"project","title":"Navigating to a sync-up detail","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"We will wrap the application built so far in a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NavigationStack"},{"type":"text","text":" so that we can navigate to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the detail screen. To do this we will create a new root-level feature that will be responsible","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"for implementing the logic of the stack and integrating all of the features together."}],"role":"project","estimatedTime":"20min","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/SyncUpDetailNavigation"},"chapter2.png":{"identifier":"chapter2.png","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/ComposableArchitecture\/chapter2.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":null,"type":"image"},"chapter4.png":{"identifier":"chapter4.png","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/ComposableArchitecture\/chapter4.png"}],"alt":null,"type":"image"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/SyncUpForm":{"url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/syncupform","kind":"project","title":"Sync-up form","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"We will create a new feature with the Composable Architecture that is capable of editing the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"details of a new sync-up. We will also add some nuanced logic around how focus moves through the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"feature to make things a little more interesting.","type":"text"}],"role":"project","estimatedTime":"15min","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/SyncUpForm"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/TestingListOfSyncUps":{"role":"project","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingListOfSyncUps","type":"topic","title":"Testing the list of sync-ups","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/testinglistofsyncups","estimatedTime":"5min","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The SyncUpsList feature we have built so far isn’t very complex. In fact, it only has one"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"primary action, that of deleting sync-ups from its collection. However, it can be good practice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to test new features as you add them, and in the future we will have much more complicated","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"behavior to test."}],"kind":"project"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/PresentingSyncUpForm":{"role":"project","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/PresentingSyncUpForm","type":"topic","title":"Presenting the sync-up form","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/presentingsyncupform","estimatedTime":"10min","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"We now have two features built: the sync-ups list and the sync-up form. These features do not"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"exist in isolation, but rather are meant to be integrated in a deep way. One should be able to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"navigate to the sync-up form from the list view, enter the details of a new sync-up, and then","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"add that sync-up to the root list."}],"kind":"project"},"chapter8.png":{"identifier":"chapter8.png","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/ComposableArchitecture\/chapter8.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":null,"type":"image"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/WhatIsSyncUps":{"role":"project","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/WhatIsSyncUps","type":"topic","title":"What is SyncUps?","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/whatissyncups","estimatedTime":"5min","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s start with a tour of the application we will be building. It’s called SyncUps, and it’s a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"recreation of Apple’s Scrumdinger demo application."}],"kind":"project"}}}